modules.description: Provides functions to serialize and deserialize OCaml values to and from XML and JSON strings, supporting custom type definitions. Works with OCaml's native types and user-defined variants, records, and polymorphic variants. Enables data exchange between client and server by converting complex structures into transportable string formats.

Handles JSON and XML-RPC requests by sending structured calls to a specified URL and returning parsed responses. Accepts RPC call objects and returns Lwt-promise wrapped responses. Used for interacting with web services that expose RPC endpoints, such as fetching remote data or triggering server-side actions.
